Description: Fragment of a rectangular bone spacer-bead with one rounded end preserved. Along the side three complete preserved holes and parts of a fourth one. Compare the complete object EA 86546.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.15A, lower layer (AWI - possibly from D14.17W)
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 116)
